I"3<p>My name is <strong>Can Li</strong> (Chinese: 李燦), and I am currently an assistant professor at Department of Electric and Electronic Engineering (EEE) of <strong>the University of Hong Kong (HKU)</strong>, working on analog and neuromorphic computing accelerators based on post-CMOS emerging devices (e.g. memristors), for efficient machine/deep learning, network security, signal processing, etc. Before that, I spent two years at Hewlett Packard Labs in Palo Alto, California, and obtained my Ph.D. from University of Massachusetts, Amherst, and B.S./M.S. from Peking University.</p>

